name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nice place to walk and enjoy the nature. Not so crowded if u come early, like 7 am or so.

Pay attention to the birds ‚Äúsinging‚Äù. Use the sound to locate them.

Occasionally u will see some birds grabbing some fishes for food ~~~

Take your time and walk through the different trials.

Well renovated and toilets are available.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
A Wetland nature reserve with an emphasis in Bird watching. Bring your binoculars if you have one, and you may be able to spot some migratory and exotic bird species.
The path is relatively well maintained and is suitable for a family of most ages, I have even seen elders in wheelchair being pushed around to experience nature.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Probably my favorite place in Singapore. Nice to get into nature away from the busy city areas!

So many birds to find, crocodiles to see, and general peaceful nature scenery!

If you haven't visited, you should!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: The man made drops are unique and fun. A quick walk at the wetland, enjoyed the walk and scenery. I also lucky enjoy to capture the National flag üá∏üá¨during the National Day! And the mating horseshoe crab.üòÄ!  Some areas are still under construction.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Had some time alone listening to birds - though I was quite annoyed by the murder of crows who dominated one part of the mangroves (as well as some of the humans who were talking really loudly)

But that's more reflective of my inner state than anything else.

Anytime is a good time to come (maybe except in the rain) and I hope I can dro by when the winter migrants stop by and the area is full of birds

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Fun outdoor place in Singapore for some wildlife spotting. Really love having my morning and evening walk here with family. We are excited to see wild crocodiles in Singapore. The pavement are easy to walk for children and elderly.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Great times with our family today, some parts of the coast walk is closed. Good experience for children but watch them carefully. Beware of the intelligent monkeys and potentially dangerous snakes and reptiles.

Managed to see a crocodile today! Will return to get the legendary Tailless giant croc next time.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It's our national park n kept as natural as it can b. Admission is free. Boardwalk is built to make d park friendly for children n old. Small compact wheelchair can enter n move ard d park rather smoothly. There r shelters but rather far apart so it's best one comes equipped with a poncho (umbrella... can't see much). Although there r natural elements n creatures, to me it's still quite a safe park after all. Enjoy d beautiful mangroves that line d shore n spot d catfish n crabs. B careful not to step out of d pavement n destroyed d many mushrooms/toadstools/fungi that grow freely on d dead logs. Have fun exploring d park!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Quite remote to access. Ample free parking. A nice walk, mostly shaded. Tide is a factor to consider, looks a bit desolate at low tide and there are tons of trash, pretty sad sight. No crocodiles or monitor lizards in sight when i visited, just the odd mudskipper and a couple of herons.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: One of the best nature reserves in Singapore. The view is special and unique in which you won't easily find elsewhere. Many creatures and animals living in this wonderful land. Over the sea, you can also have a peak at JB city.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Awesome place to get close to wild life. Wild life is everywhere and get really close to people. They also appeared on the board walk. Is important to stay alert during tour and keep your distance from the wild life.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great place to go for the weekend, and family friendly too. Pretty easy to walk about. Saw crocodiles too, perhaps it was not the right season, so we didn't see a lot of migratory birds. There is a shuttle bus service from Kranji MRT station. Check out the timing though.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Amazing nature experience in singapore. Did not expect to find such a beautiful place. Saw many birds and animals, but unfortunately not a crocodile. We will come back another time and continue looking for crocodiles. Easy to get to with north-south line and bus 925

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: This place never fails to attracting me forever. Had been visiting this place since past many years and always find it a quiet escape from daily routine of city life. Heard there many migratory birds but seldom got chance to spot them. Only some regular birds are very common. However not surprised to spot crocodiles few times. A good place if you wish to take a walk around 3.5km loop from carpark and return. Many monitor lizards can be spotted all over the place. If you have time and wish to explore wild side of Singapore then this place is for you and family. Make sure follow the guidelines and stay on the trail.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Awesome place for nature lovers and those not so into wetlands. Shaded walkway and breezy too! Beautiful sight and enjoyed myself. It was high tide when we came. Must come again. I have 300 photos hahaha which to post ü•∞

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
This is the famous wetland reserve that the migratory birds may stopover during their long journeys. I'm not a birdwatching expert, but the reserve has lots of helpful guides and signboards to help you identify the birds that you may spot.

I'd say the reserve is divided into a western region and a eastern region. If you have limited time, skip the eastern region. Most of the points of interest are on the west, including the boardwalk and of course the wetlands.

There's a small area meant for you to spot mudskippers and horseshoe crabs. It could be a little smelly for some people though.

Apart from the plants and birds, there are also some larger creatures that you might spot. One of them is the monitor lizard. If you are lucky, crocodiles.

The best option to get here is to drive. Because you want to be prepared with lots of water, snacks and perhaps a change of clothing and shoes. Raincoats or umbrella, proper headgear and sunglasses are highly recommended, not forgetting mosquito repellent. Binoculars would be nice.

Admission is free. Parking is free.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Wonderful nature reserve with rich ecological biodiversity and it feels good looking at the mangrove forests, migratory birds, fruit bats, monitor lizards, green crested lizard, squirrels, mudskippers, fishes and even a big crocodile. Nice trails and the flora and fauna in Sungei Buloh are truly amazing (part of Coastal Trail is closed for maintenance till March 2022)

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Very impressive nature reserve watching the inter-tidal waves in mangrove coast carefully conserve/maintain by NParks Singapore. Also a haven for migratory birds during different months/seasons. Beware of the crocodiles though.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Family activity on a weekend. An interesting place to visit and has many scenic places to observed wildlife in their ecological biodiversity.

Along the coastal trail they have foot path, shelther and there is free shuttle bus from Kranji MRT.

It is a very nice place to bring the whole family for a leisure walk and even have a picnic while you enjoy the wetlands which will roughly take about 2 to 3 hours depending on your pace.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Sungei buloh is a fabulous nature reserve. Don't rush through it . Take your time and stop and look around. You will be able to see monitor lizards, crocodiles, many more¬†..

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: I was lucky to be able to spot some animals while walking here. The weather was nice too, will highly recommend if you are a nature lover!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
A nice walk in the nature.
Make sure to bring a lot of water with you,it  can also be bought at the entrance only, with cash, the machines do not accept cards.
Crocodiles, lizards, bats and birds.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Great place to have a short hike and walk with the family. Flat ground, manageable for young and old.

Still not able to catch a glimpse of the elusive crocodile yet, will keep coming and trying! Saw 3 monitor lizards though üòÅ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Amazing place for nature lovers. Can be hot so carry water. Be mindful of the animals and remember we are in their territory. Just enjoy and keep your distance if you encounter the wild animals.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Beautiful wetlands reserve. Good and well maintained footpaths, bridges and lookout points for the public to enjoy the fauna and flora in the reserve.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A splendid place which is less noise and peace. Feel relaxed walking there. Inside also have museum and bird park.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Took a walk in this nature park twice in recent weeks. The NPark people have done a great job in improving and maintaining the place for members of the public to enjoy nature while keeping nature undisturbed as far as possible.

Board walks and paths are very well constructed and safe.

Allow at least 2 hours to stroll around the area to enjoy the many variety of wild birds and plants. But be careful not to step on the monitor lizards that you might miss lying very still sunning themselves along the paths.

There are also monkeys. So don't carry supermarket plastic bags as they are known to snatch them regardless of whether you are carrying food or not.

There are signs warning about crocodiles sightings. We saw a huge one today. See photo.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Splendid nature scenery with breezing winds, along with thick lush greenery that calms the mind. Unobstructed views of the Johor across and fluffy views of the clouds above that makes the experience feel completely in tranquility and serenity of peace.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice place to walk around and enjoy nature. Do take note that coastal trail (overlooking Malaysia), has been closed since Aug 2021 and expected to re-open during March 2022 after maintenance works.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Great place for a quiet walk through nature, admission is free.
Facilities are well maintained with friendly staff.

Do be aware that 925M only operates on Sundays. So only 1 bus stop near the Kranji reservoir has buses services on other days.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Beautiful mangrove nature reserve, teeming with wildlife. Spotted a crocodile swimming in the water, hawks swooping in to catch fish, myriad of herons and waterhens. Stay still and quiet to observe small crabs and mudskippers in the mud. Not forgetting squirrels, monkeys, monitor lizards and bats under the roof.

Best to arrive 7.30-9am when tide is low so that you can see the birds fishing for breakfast and uncovered mangrove floor. Depending on the time of year, there will be different migratory birds passing by the wetlands.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Wonderful place to explore nature ! üòÄ.  Great way to absorb in the natural beauty and always get some new surprises while strolling along the pathway. Having stressful day ? Just visit this place to enjoy the landscape and nature sound to release all your tension and a good sweaty workout !üëçüôèüòä

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great adventure in the far north of Singapore. Lots of lizards, birds and if you are lucky and keep looking : crocodiles! Good for families.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A nice place to visits for walking hiking jogging or enjoy nature and birds photography. There are lizards but didn't see any crocodiles. From kranji mrt take bus 925m until the kranji dam for sungei buloh center or drop at the loop bustop. If you drop early by mistake just walk to the reserve. üòù

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Review for sungei buloh migratory bird trail.
Well worth the time and effort to get there.

If planning to take photos of wildlife, get there early. It is such a big place and the pace will be so slow because you'll be taking so many pictures (if you look closely). Take a cab or hire a car.

There isn't a place to eat except for vending machine drinks and snacks at the entrance.

Rain or the hot sun aren't much of a problem with roofed observation sheds and hideouts (to watch migrating birds) and so many trees that the afternoon heat is barely felt.

If going back by commute, there is a free hourly shuttle from the reserve to Kranji MRT. If going back by bus, 925M only operates on Sunday mornings (verify schedule). Impossible to get a Grab or Gojek car service from there.

Nearby is a good restaurant (Bistro Gardenasia)

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
There are 2 parts to this wetland : the old part running alongside the Buloh river and the new part running east of this river to stretch to the Kranji Reservoir Park, where the so-called ‚Äúbird nest‚Äù lookouts could be seen and the sea eagle could be spotted.

In the old section, the loop walk in the nature park is easily completed with many observatory huts to watch birds in the right season or early morning. Monitor lizards could be seen too and at low tide in the river, crocodiles too.

A beautiful wild park not to be missed.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: We took 2hrs walking and searching around , What a lovely place with those wildlife animals around. ‚ò∫Ô∏è We do met 5 iguanas in different sizes , 1 lizard , 1 small chameleon , 1mini crab,  3 spiders ,  1 alligator, 2 crocodiles, alot of siberian crane , Periophthalmini and unknown birds and fish too . And also we met some birds that near the center of the area , It makes some sounds like a dinosaur roarüôÉ I got scared at first.  Something different compared with MacRitchie, is either you reach early morning or come later before evening, some regular visitors do say that sometimes they have a resident owl resting near the entrance tree there .

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It's a nice entertainment place, for us to bring children and kids to feel the natural beauty...I saw more than 5 crocodiles and many  Monitor lizards and owls, bats and eagles and colorful fishes... children are enjoyed...need one big round walk at the park taking more than 2-4 hours...all getting tired while walk...kids and unable to walk big round...fishers man entertained to fishing outside the gates...

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
The wetlands of Sungei Buloh are a dream come true for keen nature lovers. At this sprawling 87-hectare ecological site, you can catch migratory birds escaping the cold on their way to the warmer climes of Australia‚Äìwith some having come as far away as Siberia.

Elsewhere, crabs, mudskippers and mud lobsters can be found in their natural habitats, and viewed from a distance at observation posts that dot the park. In the reserve it is easy to notice migratory birds, Crocodile, Monitor Lizards, Mangrove forests.

Wide shot of migratory bird at Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
The Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve is a world-class eco-tourism experience first discovered in 1986 by a group of birdwatchers from the Malayan Nature Society.

Three years later, the site was designated as a nature park by the government in 1989, and officially opened in 1993. To properly experience the wetlands, you can take the free guided tours, while activities like art classes and a prawn farming demonstration will keep you busy the whole day.

If you want to take a break from the concrete jungle of the city, head to this ecological gem in the north-east of Singapore for a breath of fresh air.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Loved this place, one of the few nature reserves that make Singapore so beautiful. Lovely fish and birds to be spotted not to mention interesting reptiles .. a must visit if you're a nature lover

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great birdwatching location, especially during migratory season. Plenty of crocodile sightings as well, must go for nature lovers.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Excellent place to watch migratory birds and get in touch with nature! Go on weekday to enjoy the tranquility. Don‚Äôt miss out the wild life like crocodiles, monitor lizards! Do go on the board walk to view the mangroves that is a natural carbon sink!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Edited on 6 sep 2022
Sad to say this, the free shuttle bus has stopped and switched to a new bus shuttle service that starts way later and it cost $5 for an all day trip (only option I think?).

Very nice reserve. Please maintain low volume when you visit as it will scare the wild life here. Many birds that I was trying to capture got spooked by noisy visitors. Please be mindful that you are visitors not the residents of the nature reserve.

Do take note that the public bus 925M only operates on Sunday.

However Nparks do provide free shuttle bus on Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
located on the North easterly tip of Singapore,  the sungei buloh wetlands is probably the country's only last untouched piece of nature.
Yes there are bridges and concrete pathways around the wetlands (which isn't large when compared to any of the reservoirs) but it is as close to nature as you will find in the urban jungle that is Singapore.
The walking trails have bird lookout points in selected areas and we were lucky to see a salt water crocodile hanging out in the mangrove.
Parking is quite limited and so is shelter when it starts to rain in the middle of your walk.
A great place to visit when you want to escape the hustle of city life.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Very relaxing and very beautiful scenery.
Best to visit on the day with fine weather and clear visibility! Bring water bottle to hydrate yourself. Photos taken around 10 am.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nature reserve... Many wild animals ranging from big monitor lizards, cobras, crocodiles, migratory birds (egret, heron, eagles) and many mosquitoes. Bring along a mosquitoes repellent and watch your steps along the way be careful of passing snakes and sun bathing monitor lizards. Take a pciture of the emergency contact number on the sign board in case of any emergency situations like snake bites...

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Easy to navigate , quiet and peaceful. Able to spot different bird species. Crocodile signs make the trip more ‚Äúexciting‚Äù. Be prepared to spend more than half a day to cover the entire reserve. Is a place you can keep on going back.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice walk. 2-3h taking your time. Saw snakes, crocodiles, red moss, praying mantis fishes and lots of birds.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Lovely nature walks. You can look over to Malaysia. Very popular with bird watchers.
We didn't see any crocodiles, but according to the warning signs, there are some.
Bring plenty of water, sunscreen and snacks. There is a vending machine at the visitor center, but with limited choice.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: You have to be quiet and keep your eyes peeled to catch sight of the more interesting wildlife...It is as huge as many other wetlands but for a small area, you can get very lucky with some resilience...

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A very different setting one may find here compared to other parts of Singapore. Very close with nature and the wetlands wildlife. Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve allows singaporeans to be away from the hustle and bustle of city life. Travelling here and out of this reserve will be difficult via public transport so do take note.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: You have to look VERY closely along the edge of the water and you‚Äôll see the üêä There are also lots of monitor lizards (scary but harmless!), birds and other wildlife. Johor is right across the water!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Awesome place to explore.
Tranquil and peaceful with sounds of nature (birds, insects)

Trail was pretty manageable with observation towers and huts around for better views.

Sighted:
Puffer Fish, Fishes, Birds, Owl, Monitor Lizard, small snake, bats.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Great place to walk. Lookout for mangrove inhabitants, migratory birds, squirrels, monitor lizards..and if you are lucky, crocodiles.
Coastal walk is closed at the moment though.
Bring a cap, wear sun block.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Beautiful place to visit and hike. Many wildlife too look out for. Not crowded

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Finally, managed to make it to the other far end of the island for that long awaited explorations.

One thing to note, the best experiences are seen & felt thru the heart as well.  A few firsts here, first crocodile sighting, then owl, bat, egret, heron.

Super lovely & ended up at Poison Ivy for the reward.  Yummy nice back to basic comfort food...
Fur baby was tired out & gave a lesson on how to do power nap & beauty sleep.
Fyi, pets are not allowed in nature park & he was off having a field day elsewhere

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Had a great fun at Sungei Buloh nature reserve. The cloudy weather is Best time to spot animals in the wild. Good workout for everybody and we really played the spot the animal game. We had such a fruitful trip witnessing bird preying on the fish and green snakes on the little tree. Has such a great fun I wish I can return soon on another cloudy day! Great family outing to help the teenagers to forget about playing electronic gadget, other than taking photos!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Good place to take a walk. But pray with good weather. Or else  prepare umbrella üåÇ.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: great place to see wildlife...birds, fishes, monitors,  crocodiles, and greenery.it would be great if the restricted area could be open to public from time to time, like Kranji Marshes do.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Inaccessible but worth the trip. A place where if you heighten your senses, you can see a lot of creatures that lives amongst us in their natural habitat in one of the last mangrove swamps in Singapore. A good educational tour to bring the kids and children along, where they can see a lot of insects, reptiles that we don't usually see in the increasingly urban jungle we live in. Lucky to see quite a fair bit this trip...

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Singapore's 1st ASEAN Heritage Park! The only place to see wild Saltwater Crocodiles. And many more amazing mangrove flora & fauna. Explore with a licensed nature guide to spot the hidden wildlife.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
One of the few places in singapore can spend whole day without entry fee..

From kranji mrt you can take bus to Sungei wetland. This place is amazing. Crocodiles can be everywhere in this area. Actually people don‚Äôt wanted to go inside the forest to explore. They just stop around the admin office and come back, but if you walk inside through wetlands, under the shadows of trees. The feel is wonderful.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve is a very huge place, when you walk in to it you feel like you're in a forest (actually it is one). You can see types of animals and plants there, for example of animal are monitor lizards and squirrels. But if you're lucky you may even get to meet a crocodile üêä there. Well Sungei Buloh is definitely a great place to go if you're a person who likes to explore new things.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Very nice afternoon walk, surrounded by wild life of the non-dangerous sort... As long as one stays on the walking path and don't do stupid things.
My first visit after years of procrastinating because I thought it was too far away.
My first lesson about migratory birds: why there aren't many in July/Aug. ü§¶

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Went at 730am and caught the beautiful sun rays. Managed to catch the resident crocodile floating around!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Fun place to be able to see some wildlife if you are lucky (lizards, crocodiles, bats, owls) next to the regular birds nesting and resting there

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Already visited a few times. This place has a lot of crocodiles and monitor lizards. If you want to see crocodiles go to the main brige or the buloh tidal ponds center part. Go during low tide or you probably won't see any crocodiles.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Very nice nature place.  Came with kids... must prepare the kids to walk alot.  Hence, bring lotsa water and some snacks for the kids as energy fuel for them
Will definitely come again.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great place for a long walk fully immersed in nature. Wild vegetation, many spots for bird watching and, if lucky, crocodiles too. Highly recommended, perfectly served with parking lots and bus stops. Early morning time recommended.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Spend the public holiday afternoon with nature üåø lots of greenery and chilling weather. There‚Äôs bird watching shelters throughout the trail, however this time isn‚Äôt the season, only a few birdies on-site.
Didn‚Äôt meet the monkey along the way as well but really glad we spotted a crocodileüêä and a snake above our head. Very exciting experience üëåüèªüôåüèº

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Pretty place for a nice stroll (take the coastal trail) and you may even catch sight of some of its wild inhabitants along the way!!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: OK this place is pretty big... prob need 2 hours or more to complete. Love the wetlands area to the west where u can spot many animals n birds.. my 1 hr walk saw monitor lizards, a Croc, heron and wow a King Cobra.. latter not my fav.. many parking areas and v nice paved walking ways.. good guest reserve office too w clean nice toilets.. üëå üëç

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Do not eat in open as there may be monkeys stealing your food. Plenty of monitor lizards and look out for the occasional croc!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Fully opened and good place for hiking or leisure. Remember to bring mosquito repeller.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
One of the long walk trail you can experience in Singapore. The place opens at 7 AM, its good to reach at opening time to see the beautiful sunrise.

1) Good place for nature lover
2) Beautiful place to witness Sunrise
3) Moderate walk - nearly 4-5 km in total (including Coastal Trail, Forest Trail, Mid-canopy walk and Migratory Bird Trail)
4) This place is famous for Bird photography. you can find nearly 6 hiding place for bird photography
5) if you are lucky, you can witness crocodiles and Monitor lizards

Things to carry:
1) enough water and snacks (please do not litter)
2) binocular for kids
3) umbrella

Transport connectivity:
2 Car parks.
15 min travel by public transport(Bus # 925) from Kranji MRT station

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Perfect place for families with young kids. Good place for them to get close to nature. Don‚Äôt miss the other nearby attractions south of here.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: bring your kidsÔºå enjoy hikingÔºåbird and crocodile watchingÔºåphotographing thereÔºÅ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Was raining during the hike but a nice  tranquil experience. Happen to find two monitor lizards and a crocodile. Also a strange paranormal experience of hearing chanting which can cannot be traced.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nice for a morning walk, walked from the visitor centre (sungei buloh wetland reserve extension) to the wetland centre, looped around the migratory bird trail, and back to the visitor centre. In total approx 3.5h, started at 7.30am. Spotted crocodiles, monitor lizards, mudskippers, various bird species. Went in August, but recommended to visit Sept-Mar during the migratory period to see more wildlife. The extension is wheelchair friendly although the main wetland area not as much. Take note, the pathway along the migratory bird trail is sandy.

Would be nice to catch the sunrise here, along with a view of malaysia right across (eagle point lookout area)

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Lively and lovely place . I am glad that Singapore is turning this nature land to more accessible for people to visit.
Unfortunately there is tons of rubbish at the wetland . This is not because Singapore is not cleaning the park but they comes from the ocean . I think picking the rubbish might be challenging because of the mangrove roots .
Hopefully one day the selfish people can stop littering ‚Ä¶

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Can‚Äôt believe it‚Äôs Singapore!! Saw hugging lizards. Guess if they were mating or wrestling üòâ cute flying fish greeted us as well. Didn‚Äôt see crocs and other wildlife, but the nature and tranquility around was üòç (portions of the trek are closed - FYI)

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A great place to go to spend your time. Best to visit early morning. Easy to reach via public transport. The area on the way to the reserve looks unlike anywhere else in Singapore - almost underdeveloped compared to the cityscape across the island. Has its own charm. Unfortunately or fortunately we didn‚Äôt see crocs during our visit.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Get there by taking the free shuttle service (available only weekends and on Public Holidays) from Kranji. There are 4 stops in total - Kranji MRT, Sungei Buloh Visitor Center, Sugei Buloh Wetlands Center, and Kranji Marshes. It's very convenient if you time your visit for each stop carefully. Be prepared however to take the public bus 925 when the shuttle service gets full around 1pm to 3pm.

Enjoyed the walk at each stop, and the boardwalks were well-maintained. You'll see many bird watchers. It's generally less crowded and a much more enjoyable nature walk than at MacRitchie as all the trails are paved (no mud) and there's somehow no mosquitoes there. So comfortable attire like sports shoes or sandals (hiking boots not needed) and light sports wear (shorts, t-shirt) are perfect.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
A sunny day @SG (Sungei Buloh) Wetland Reserve.

Pity that parts of the trail is closed for maintenance.

From Eagle ü¶Ö Point, JB is so near but yet out of reach.

This one of the hidden jem which is a good place to explore with family or friends.

Remember to bring plenty of water and pack some fruits, sandwiches and snack.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It's a natural place to chill out , if u r lucky can spot lizards, birds , snake and others . Very greenery.well kept and clean

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Very great wetland reserve. Sad that we didn't see any crocodile. Amazing friendly staff at the smaller visitor center.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nice weather are walking under the trees in the morning, suitable bringing kid's to here for looking natural habitats. Our s'poreüá∏üá¨ natural unearth a world filled with rich biodiversity park.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: I have good experience visiting this place.  Can see the view of johor from sungei buloh, can see also some animals.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: The place was just opposite with Johor, Malaysia. This place is good for hiking /walking trail lovers. If you love walking more closer to nature, then this place is very suits for you.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Family oriented nature walk, easy peasy for young n old! Nice photography üòúüôÇ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Like the coastal trail so much. Definitely a nice place to trek. Suitable for family. Picnic is prohibited here in the reserve so please do not bring picnic food unless some bite to eat to prevent hungry as you need to keep hydrate and energy to walk around.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Easy access with car and public bus. Can see crocodiles during low tide. I saw otter, big monitor lizard on the walking path, big crocodile (famous tailess croc), mud skipper, flamingo, turtle, fish, etc.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Liked the quiet environment for a walk enjoying the scenery and bird spotting

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Always my preferred place for nature walk. If lucky, can spot shore birds or the crocodiles.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Incredible nature reserve. I've been to many similar ones and this one was the best. The layout really allows you to observe all the birds clearly without disturbing them. Seeing the crocodiles and monitor lizards everywhere was really special, too!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Well maintained wetland reserves. Had a fait bit of wildlife to see but the oil slicks and rubbish in the swamps did take away some of the charm.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Awesome place for a walk, a lot of wildlife can be spotted.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A nice path that reminds you of what Singapore used to be like

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice place to have a jogging or nature walk. The combination of sea view and forest. Not crowded. Breathe fresh air. A lil bit far and remote, driving to the location is recommended. Nearby there is a nice restaurant (Bistro) to chill out. They sell many beautiful plants and house decoration too. Good place for family outing!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
It‚Äôs quite remoted but considered as accessible as it can be reached by public transport. It looks very big from the map, but it‚Äôs quite fast to walk from one end to another end.

I went to the coastal trail to be on those observation pod. The iconic kingfisher pod is on this trail too. I got to take a lot of instagrammable pics and managed to see the crocodile and some birds.

The mud experience was closed due to maintenance. So bad. I wanted to walk on the net bridge.

After you reached the wetland center, you can continue to walk to the wetland to watch birds. It was raining suddenly so I didn‚Äôt proceed.

Make sure to bring your water and food, also take away your rubbish before leave. I saw some rubbished on the bush. It‚Äôs bad for the environment as some materials are not bio degradable and wild animals might consume them and kill themselves. Please be considerate.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: One of our all-time favourite nature hangouts. The migratory bird trail is a short and easy trail for adults and kids. Keep a lookout for estuarine crocodiles, migratory and resident birds, monitor lizards, squirrels, dog-faced fruit bats and snakes. If heading to the mangrove trail, remember to apply mosquito repellent.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: If you have more time go to migratory bird path. However went to the forest track and its manageable for two young kids. They were excited to see mudskippers , crossing the hanging bridge, identifying small creatures along the way. Too bad there are lots of trash swept away from the sea that stuck between mangrooves.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A free wetland reserve, which is across the sea with Malaysia. The scenery and experience are great, but the location is far away from downtown, only NO.925 bus can reach the entrance. There are many animals but you need to be very careful to find them.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Great place to visit with your family to enjoy nature.

Plenty of wildlife if you're lucky, and equally as many nature photographers waiting around to capture it's beauty.

Do watch out for spiders in the branches and the occasional monitor lizards.

There's a great lookout hut overlooking Johor.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Highly recommend arriving just before opening time (7 am) if you want to avoid crowds. Great for a walk or birding. Paths are well defined. There is no concession here so bring water. Great for the photography of migratory birds. You need a 400mm lens or more. Watch for the crocodiles. We saw a couple of them. We also saw eagles and egrets and kingfisher.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A very nice place for nature lovers and wildlife photographers. Lots of endemic species can be spotted here, including bats, monitor lizards, crocodile and even king cobra. It is also one of the main habitat for migratory birds and there are a lot of hideout built for long range photography.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Be prepared to walk alot, spent 2-3 hrs here to cover the entire park and even spotted some crocodiles!

However this place is very inaccessible so when leaving, do check out the shuttle bus timings! Else it'll be a long walk out to the main road to take a bus üòÖ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
What an adventure!

So raw. So pure. So natural.

I have been wanting to visit Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve for ages. I made it today finally! I felt like I was travelling out of SG.

NParks is doing a great great job of preserving the nature at its best. THANK YOU!

From the well-maintained landscape, mangrove areas, bird viewing areas, cleanliness of public areas, all can't be possibly done without the thorough planning and the dedication of the workers - Your truly foreign workers for their good work.

A highly recommended place to explore if you love nature. It was like stepping into the not-so-Singapore side of Singapore overseeing Malaysia.

Nonetheless, the Reserve might not be the best place for young kids if they are scared of the sound of nature, sights of wild animals, forestry landscape, to name a few.

We spotted so many wild plants and of course wild animals as well.

Reminder:

1) There's only one way in and out within the Reserve unless you walk along the main road. So, please plan ahead - your route and your energy level.

2) FREE shuttle bus service available during PH and weekends.

3) Choose your car park based on your need - bird viewing or mangrove trails to save you time and energy

4) Bring an umbrella or a stick. I felt safer

5) Check the weather

6) Check the tide - it determines what you might want to see

You're welcome üòä

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Crave to get closer to nature? This is a must visit for all to understand biodiversity in Singapore. Wide range of mangrove flora, migration birds & wild life (otters, jumping fishes, hornbills, monkeys, monitor lizards, crabs & etc) can be spotted at different time of the year. Awesome hiking  place for family or group of friends to explore & experience nature. 3-4 hours visit time should be planned excluding transportation/ travel time.
The Park is under going upgrading with new walkway being pathed. This does not affect the park visit. Weather can get quite warm & humid. Drink plenty of water the night before and bring bottled water, cap/ hat, towel & raincoat for sudden rainfall. Enjoy the hike, listen to the nature calls & keep your eyes opened for nature surprises :)

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Was pretty crowded on a Sunday morning but such a fun place to explore! There are a few trails to explore. Lots of unique birds to see, as well as monkeys, crocodiles, spiders and other animals. But they don‚Äôt bother you so not to worry.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Sungei Buloh is one of my favourites nature park. It's a good place to see monitor lizard, migrate birds, mud skippers, and crocodile if you are lucky. It is one place where I would visit a few times a year!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Our first time to Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve on a Monday afternoon to avoid crowds.  It was very quiet and peaceful trail at 5plus.

Note: only bus to go there during weekdays is bus 925.

Going there during weekdays are quite inconvenient and inaccessible as walking will take you hours to arrive, so we took a taxi in.

The trail is very peaceful and quiet perhaps the time is quite short for us, saw squirrels üêø but didn‚Äôt caught any sight of crocodile and other reptiles.üêä it‚Äôs a pity.  Would want to explore again next time.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: This is a very popular bird photography place amongst the photography enthusiasts in Singapore. Migratory birds escapinht form harsh winter would stop over here before heading south to Indonesia.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Visited Sungei Buloh wetland with my family. It was a lovely walk in the park that my kids managed to see iguana, bats, crocodile and many more small.animals and fishes. There are also many wild flowers and insects in the woods. Parking was convenience and free. Remember to bring along water, cap and insect repellent. These will come in handy.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
The drive there itself is so amazing. Plenty of carpark lots. (There are bus services to the entrance to.)
No further info. Have fun exploring!!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice area for leisure walk. I guess it's a great place to explore with family (especially when you can show young children on wild life animals like crocodiles and various types of birds). Seen quite lot of people bringing professional bird viewing equipment for the birds here. was lucky today to be able to catch a view of crocodiles and eagles.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Lovely, well designed wetland reserve. Sadly, maintenance and upkeep leave a lot to be desired. Temporary signs placed across a number of paths to indicate they are under maintenance have grown algae and lichen, yet nothing by way of maintenance appear to have been done. At low tide, the mangroves are littered with plastic trash. The place needs a clean-up badly.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Had a great, chill stroll along the various trails available in the evening. Come during low tides and give yourself 3 to 4 hours if you want to slowly check out all the viewing hides/platforms and spot wildlife!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Love this place- only problem is it is painful to get to and from. Taxi there is fine, but always struggle to get a taxi or ride hail back.
Amazing nature- almost always see crocodiles, usually snakes and countless species of birds!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Great day trip option if you want to lose the CBD hustle and bustle. There are clear walking paths so you don't have to worry too much about getting dirty (except for a few unpaved sections).

There are a lot of good spots for pictures. Plan to spend two to three hours if you want to see all of the reserve.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: You can enjoy a peaceful day out with your loved ones. Great place for bird watchers and nature enthusiasts alike. Might be a bit inaccessible for those without cars.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
I was the first to enter when the gate opened at 7am and enjoyed the serenity.
Beautiful sunrise, the sound of nature, the forest bathing is awesome!
This place would be perfect if is not so manicured.
Insect repellent is a must.

But I won‚Äôt say the same once it past 8am.
The crowd start coming in, noisy big group and it just ruin your experience.
Despite the ambassador around, people are still forming their own big group more than the allowed size.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It is a nice and easy walk (2 hours) that suits people of different ages. We spotted some exotic animals including a salt water crocodile. There are hide-outs to observe migratory birds which is around from Sept to March. It is highly educational for kids.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nice place for easy hike .. lot of birds and reptile üòç.
Amazing experience. Kids will love this hike . Less people on weekends can enjoy peace hike. Not recommend hike alone. Those using bus transportation you have to return back to kranji way bus stop. üòâ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: On a hot weather make sure you have a sun hat, sunblock and mosquito repellent. Be aware of where you walk and steps, as you will easily encounter monitor lizard, snakes, spiders and croc. Great place to view migrating birds into the area. Make sure you have bags for garbage as bins not easily accessible in the area, not to forget to mention your drinking water. Grab a map to find Yr nearby public toilet and access to vending machine for beverage n snacks.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Amazing place! Worth all the haste to be here

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: The one place that is very close to the nature. A morning of just walking in silence and observing the peace of mother nature. Its tranquil is very soothing to the soul, and body. Seeing all the beings like birds, fish, and squirrel teaches us of the freedom. On a fine lucky day you might catch a glimpse of the crocodiles there. Its amazing...

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Wonderful place for dates/family outings/light exercise/change of pace. This place is simply amazing, all for the low low price of $0.00. There's all kind of animals there, horseshoe crabs, hornbills, crocodiles, mudskippers, golden orbweaver spiders, monitor lizards are just a few that I spotted within my two trips here so far. Be sure to pack some water, insect repellent, and an umbrella in case dark clouds start looming while you're there. Also be sure to hold onto your hat at some of the more open areas as the breeze can be pretty amazing. Do be sure to read through the park rules to make sure this reserve continues to be a wonderful place for future generations.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Very nice place and one of the least man made one I've seen here in Singapore. The pathway is made to complete the nature, not to disturb it. Lots of interesting facts and mostly plants to discover - as naturally animals are mostly shy (other than herons and bugs) - and that's how it should be (you probably don't really want a crocodile crossing your path). There are small vending machines at both entrances and toilets so no worries comfort wise.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Be prepared to walk on unpaved roads. It consists of two parts. One thing that irritates me the most more than the mosquitoes are the noisy people, especially aunties and uncles there. Feel free to ask them to keep quiet as it is part of the rules to maintain a low sound level. Nice hides and observation screens for viewing. Bring a binoculars as the birds are still pretty far from the watching areas. Recommended to go during low tide so check the tide timings on that day.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Started at 10am. Luckily it was quite shady with lots of trees. Took me about 2.5hrs to complete walking the entire park. Saw Crocodiles, monitor lizard, monkeys, fishes, stray dogs and big spiders along the way especially at the wetlands. Enjoyed myself very much.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A good place to touch nature, especially mangrove. Take mrt to kranji stop and take bus 925. There are four routes and coast line has onion-like buildings. On my way to wetland, I saw monkeys, giant mudskipper, crabs. Some places are still under construction. A good place for weekends and friends.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: One of my favourite nature park - lot of fauna to spot. Beautiful landscape during high tide and lots of waterbirds during low tide. And of course fauna typical for a wetland from mudskippers to horseshoe crabs to monitor lizards. And watch out for those crocs :-)

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nature at its Best!
Authorities have done well in balancing the build up and not disturbing the natural habitat around it. This place is worth visiting if you love nature! üòäüëçüèº

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Come early, enjoy the walking trails. The eastern park has built up walkways and features like the Kingfisher Pod. Gets a good view of the straits. The western part are the tidal ponds which would take an hour to loop around. Some public members may be noisy which would inhibit birds and animals, so avoid them if you want to observe and pick out their calls.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
If you want to sight a crocodile in its natural habitat Sungei Buloh is the place to visit. Plus it‚Äôs a paradise for migratory birds due to its marshland landscape, which pulls in a lot of photographers from around.

We reached very early to avoid the crowd. The place has been well maintained since I had visited last and I hope it is continued that way. The place is famous for its mudskippers and they are quite easy to spot, so look out for them.

There are 3 trails around the Reserve and one of them shares the view of Malaysian skyline which is beautiful.

Definitely a recommended place to visit and spend good time with friends and family alike. And don‚Äôt forget to put on your sunblock üß¥.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A great place to see and learn about nature and mangroves wetlands. And so we saw the birds, squirrels, spiders, giant mudskippers, fishes, snakes ... although we didn't get to see the elusive crocodiles or sea otters. The paths/tracks have been made easier to walk and shelters provided within easy reach in case of inclement weather. The 3 of us enjoyed our hike and nature and we saw families with children also appreciated the trip & experience there.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Amazing walking path with many dedicated area for brief watching.
Drinking water available.
Mostly shady areas.
Went on Wednesday not much crowd.
By bus: bus stop closeby to the entrance but return you have to walk along the same route to catch the bus. That‚Äôs the most tiring part.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Tip go early. By 8am the carpark is almost full save for one or two remaining lots.

Honestly, the last time I have been here must have been at least 10 years ago. Looks like the reserve has gotten larger. The park is adding a new bridge that will be commissioning soon.

We came to see the crocs. Boy did we see them. Spotted 3! One probably swam across the Straits üòÇ! Monitor lizards aplenty, big and small, all love to bask in the sun. At the centre, look up and you can see a family of bats zzzing away. Lots of fish in the waters too. It was high tide when we went so we could see the waters going into the reserve. They looked like rapids with the inter tidal changes. Nice!

It was shady with the foliage cover but not much shade at the coastal trail. Well, it‚Äôs the closest to visiting Malaysia at this point! Watch for your telco provider on your phone saying Welcome to Malaysia! *cheap thrill eh?*

Trails were relatively flat, some had new broadwalk put in. So easy for strollers and wheelchairs so long as you stay on the path.
No bicycle riding in the reserve, do that outside. Park has alot of visitors on the weekend.

It was a nice walk. Glad we managed to see the birds, insects, reptiles that we wanted to see - all in their natural habitat!

Keep the wetland clear of rubbish to be enjoyed by generations to come. ‚úåüèªüêä

5 stars, just for the rich wildlife the park has (including humans üò¨).

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice nature walk! About 2-3 hours for the whole reserved park. A lot of trees so the walk paths are shaded, a good and refreshing bonding for families and friends.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Visited on weekday & had a pleasant stroll through the reserve. It was relatively empty on weekday morning which was great. Observed many monitor lizards, crocodiles, and migratory birds. Took us 4h for our hike and we haven‚Äôt even managed to finish the entire park. Entered the wetland reserve which took us 1h around the entire circle which was pretty tiring. Nice structures around for photography :)
Took a bus 925 from Kranji mrt.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Singapore's no.1 nature reserve. Too good miss... perfect for nature lovers. Go early and enjoy the walking trails, enjoy nature but also 'swampland" odour at certain area. Don't forget sunblock, water and mozzie repellent. You will want come back again and again.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Well maintained. Many renovation and refurbishment activities to make this nature park be even better. There is a public bus 925M from Woodlands during Sunday/ Public Holiday. They also provide free shuttle bus during weekends and Public Holiday from Kranji MRT station.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Enjoy the greenery & fresh air. Watch the crocodile and birds while looking at JB @another side of strait. Feel like just one step far away. Hopefully can go to JB soon.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Tranquil greenery, wild animals like Otters, Crocs, Monitor lizards, mud crabs, owls and other migratory birds.

Sea, swamp, lots of great lookout points and view of Malaysia's coastal line.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Went there on Sat morning, was really quite crowded. It's easy path, good for beginner. Pretty scenery. I did not get to see crocodile though üòÖ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Really pleasant 2hr trail between the trees and marshland. Get a clear view of Malaysia across the Sg straits and look out for some animal sightings!

It‚Äôs a 1.3km trek from the further car park towards the wetlands and another 2km loop trail. Trails are well paved, flat and senior friendly.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Well maintained trails suitable for all types of hikers. Numerous viewing pods and observation decks along the trail to take in the abundant wildlife. Came across a big monitor lizard along the way.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: One of the place that you can hear crickets in broad daylight. A nice view of Johore and natural swamps and wildlife. Saw a monitor lizard while walking in the park. There are bored watchers with the long lenses trying to snap pics of migratory birds feeding at the swamp lands. A must go at least once in a lifetime for Singaporeans.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
This is wonderful place to enjoy on weekend. You can take your kid to here to enjoy nature atmosphere. There have spectacular landscape. With the modern architecture.
Be careful with crocodiles on the trail.
So impressive with spiral snail observation tower.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Wetland Reserve with great biodiversity. Spend some time exploring the trails, spotting and learning about the animals, insects and mangrove trees. Guaranteed to have a great time being so close to nature.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It was sunny morning and pleasant to walk with the kids. Nice view from this eagle viewing point to see the wild animals not in cages.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A nice place to hike for the family. Manage to catch some birds and small animals in the wetland area. It was also very near to JB. We could see the high rise from there.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Coming on a weekday, the reserve is deserted except a few groups of visitors, providing an excellent opportunity to enjoy the true nature of the surroundings. The travelling time to the place is far and I would only recommend coming here if you have private transport.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Witnessed the wildlife despite the rain on New Year‚Äôs Day. Learnt about migratory species that fly across Asia Pacific region.

Heard from a park regular about Tail-less the crocodile, aka the ‚Äòmascot‚Äô of the park who‚Äôs pretty known to visitors and regulars. Tail is thought to have been lost in a fight. A strong crocodile which has survived for 12 years and counting.

Photos: a young monitor lizard having its feast on a decaying fish, migratory birds having a rest on the sand bank

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Beautiful wetland reserve. Highly recommend others to go. Lots of amazing flora and fauna to see.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: love this place! good for a ~9km hike with plenty of things to see. saw a number of animals in the brochure on a good day. maybe because it was rainning the night before.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Very nice place for bird watching. The path is a loop of 2.3 km and there are several observation points and an observation tower for you to watch for migratory and non migratory birds. If you're lucky you'll be able to spot a crocodile or two

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Awesome place to look for crocodiles or birds. Inspired me to take up photography again. Be sure to read up on proper safety in encountering crocodiles, the sightings here are daily and they have been known to come up on to the foot paths.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nice.. Weather was cool with rain.. Real wetland experience.
Spotted a crocodile too.. Need to be cautious since it could climb to the walkways.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
This is my second time at Sungei Buloh since circuit breaker restrictions has been eased. I wanted to go back to catch a glimpse of the crocodile after I saw a hiker spotted it and posted it on social media.

Today was a great day! and I spotted two crocodiles at the wetland reserve! What a lucky day!~ Spotted one five minutes into my trek and was surprised to see it hiding under a shade.

There are pros and cons of going on a Sunday morning. It is expected to have more visitors on Sundays as families bring along their children for a hike, and maids were there doing their photo shoots maskless (hmmm)... However, the advantage is that since many people are trekking and looking out for animals, they will be able to point out these animals and you will be able to enjoy the fun too.

It is understandable that visitors at the reserve will not be able to observe the one meter social distancing rules as it was really crowded this morning with many children and families. I'm perfectly fine with that as some of the trails and platforms are narrow and it is impossible for all visitors to observe that. If you are conscious of social distancing, weekends might not be the right time of you.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice place to visit outside the concrete jungle of Singapore. Can watch sunrise if you are able to reach there early before 7. Watch eagles fishing along the seashore. Those who appreciate Mother Nature would not regrets to visit this place.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Nice scenery with lots of animals to see. Only thing is it can be a bit hot when the sun is out. Otherwise just hope for wind. Can see mangroves, storks, herons, owls, monitor lizards, crocodiles, spiders, other birds.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Walks are nicely marked. Lots of wildlife to look out for. Good info on flora and fauna. Very educational and well laid out.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
A therapeutic walk that is away from the usual bustling city and crowded Park Connectors. A good respite time to immerse yourself in Mother Nature.

But of course, be careful of crocodiles and other reptile creatures. After all, this is their home.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: So beautiful!! Good to bring mosquito repellent but please don‚Äôt overspray it...didn‚Äôt spot the legendary crocodile but many cute snakes! Can‚Äôt wait to visit it again!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Went to the park around 4pm, it was such a peaceful, relaxing and beautiful nature reserved.

Managed to spot the iconic crocodile next to the wooden bridge.

Was super lucky upon exiting the park exit, cause an oriental hornbill landed on a tree across the road mere meters away from me. It stayed in the tree for a good few minutes before it took off.

Love the nature reserved, highly recommended for everyone.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A rare place of wilderness surrounded by development. Might see lizard and crocs if lucky. Great for birdwatching. Easy access to all age groups.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great place to be for time in nature

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: This place was amazing! Loads of animals, nice walk, views of the jungle and Malaysia, feels like you are on a trip away from home right in your back yard. Plenty of amenities to get water and food if needed. Go and enjoy the afternoon.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Nice place to see nature, see crocodile in the wild. Definitively a good place to bring kids to introduced them to nature while doing a bit of hiking. Just be aware and follow the signs. There are clean bathrooms and drinking fountains  to soothe the thirst.

review_text: A relaxing place to go, great view, and plenty of directory panel along the path. Only downside is bunch dead fishes and rubbish float along the lumnitzera walk.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: This section of SBWL has many places for bird watching. It‚Äôs nice to walk around the wetland and be able to see the egrets, a crocodile (resting) and water monitor lizard (having lunch). Nice place to bring children to enjoy the outdoor in Singapore.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
It's really amazing to discover the beauty and wonders of Nature at Singapore‚Äôs first ASEAN Heritage Park. It's uncover a world filled with rich biodiversity as you wander through the wetlands with an extensive mangrove forest of Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve.

You can cover many trails and discover its native inhabitants such as mudskippers, crabs, shellfish, water snakes, birds, spiders, monitor lizards and otters. Admire the beauty of resident birds such as herons, kingfishers and sunbirds.

I took public transport to reach there..
Go to Kranji MRT Station then take bus 925 from there. It will drop you at Kranji Reservoir Carpark B then walk across the road to the Visitor Centre...

Enjoy! üòÄ

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It‚Äôs a nice quiet place for nature lover, it‚Äôs not that hot even on a sunny days. Can see many salt water crocodiles if you are lucky enough.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
First time coming here with my family for hiking. Good place for a nature walk. Tried to catch some glimpse of crocodile but too bad don‚Äôt have. However, we manage to see monitor lizards and squirrels.

Note: please prepare mosquito patch, insect repellent and sunblock in advance.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
A good outing with friends and family, very educational and great wildlife/outdoor exposure for everyone. During our walkabout, we manage to spot a lot of different types of birds, insects, and animals. (E.g. red ant nest, bird nest, small snakes, monitor lizard, snakehead fish, bats, birds, etc).

Entrance is free, there are also cold water dispenser, and clean toilet. Public bus to this area is very frequent. Overall great experience and highly recommend!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: A large nature reserve with mangrove swamps. Unique nature experience. Exploring the whole place took around 2 hours.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Very nice place for a morning walk close to the nature and fresh air. Now even easier with their recent park connector upgrade.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great place to take your kids, especially when you don't want to pay SGD33 to visit the zoo. The 3 km nature trail is moderately easy and good exercise for both kids and elderly. If you have difficulty spotting animals just ask any of the numerous photography enthusiast there and they will happily point you in the direction of the nearest animal.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
I went here last week to enjoy wildlife.
Just 1 hour from the center of the city, You can find many kind if birds, reptiles, etc here.
To go there, I use Kranji MRT station and Grab.
Ba careful that sometimes it takes time to catch Grab or taxi at the site.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Excellent variety of mangroves. While there is lots of Birdlife, the usual target species are on the shy side. Lots of rubbish amongst the mangroves and a litter drive is needed. Well signed.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Surround by natural beauty of sea and mangrove. Good for a long stroll morning and late afternoon. Among the sea creatures,  look out for mud slippers, crabs and small fishes. Sea birds are abundant from around and johore. Try spotting migratory birds from northern n southern spheres. Please look out for crocodiles and larger animals.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great weekend visit to see the intersection of urban and wetlands in Singapore. Do plan the trip of low tide times like early morning 8.00 am  to catch the birds, monitor lizards, crocodiles. The facility is nicely maintained good spend half a day here. Great place for nature lovers!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
This is an experience I would highly recommend. There is a visitor centre here and you will get to learn about the wildlife present at the wetland. You will also learn about the migratory routes of the birds. From here, you have options for various trails. From the visitor centre, if you cross the bridge, you will enter the wetlands, where you may chance upon birds. On the other hand, you can go in the opposite direction towards the car park. From here, you can start the coast to coast trail, where you will end at Mangrove Gallery. Along the 1.3km coastal trail, there are numerous instagrammable spots, especially with the pods that are nicely shaped, and also provide shade from the sun.

Along the coast, you can also see Johor Bahru across the sea. There are signs warning of crocodiles, but none were seen on the day I was there.

I would highly recommend coming here. It will take about 1.5 hours if you slowly explore the trail and all that it has to offer. If you are using the Kranji Countryside Express bus to get here, the end point at the Mangrove Gallery also has another bus stop for you to be picked up once you're done with your coastal trail.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Escape the city and embrace nature. Go early if u want the the whole pod to yourself for photos. We reached about 7am and still pretty empty and the sunrise hue warms the photo...

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
Splendid nature park/reserve to bring the family for a bit of nature spotting. Total track distance of about 4 km. Managed to spot crocodile, monitor lizards, mudskippers and a variety of other  mangrove fauna and flora.

A bit crowded on weekend due to Singaporean not being able to travel.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: It's a nice place with quite a few scenic spots. Suitable for family and friends for a good walk around the reserve. It will be better to go during low tide so if u are lucky, u may even spot a crocodile! Other than this, there are many spots for birds lovers where they can observe in a hide. Carpark space for cars and motorcycles parking are available. Hope everybody had a good walk!!! *Cheers!!!

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Must go. Singapore's wildest open concept Jungle Safari. Open your eyes. Look for nature. You will be surprised that many hidden animals watching you.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Really cool little park, where you can follow the trail along the coast and see across to Malaysia. There are crocodiles here, although can be hard to spot so give yourself some time to wait as it is worth it! Plenty of facilities at the park entrance, including lockers and bathrooms. It is hard to get taxis to pick up from this location so be aware. There are buses that service though.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
I‚Äôm so glad we still have places like this in Singapore, where it still feels like ‚Äònature as it is‚Äô. Walking the whole loop took about <50mins (~2km) in total

Lots of egrets and herons doing their own thing in their natural habitat, a very pleasant sight! if you‚Äôre lucky, you might get to spot a crocodile üêä, lots of monitor lizards roaming around nonetheless if you would like some of the reptile action üëäüèª also plenty of fish swimming in the waters and a nice view of JB on the other side. A shame to see quite a bit of trash lying around.

4 stars mainly cause this isn‚Äôt a place I would specially visit. Just happened to want to take a cycling trip out with some friends. P.S. starting early at 7am is highly recommended

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Beautiful scenery and well kempt. You can see crabs, birds and mud skippers too. The walk is suitable for kids.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
A very pleasant morning at Sungei Buloh. Took a cab to the wetland dropoff point and did a round around the wetland. Saw crocodiles, otters, fishes, tortoise, squirrels and birds. There was little people around early morning and we spent time to soak within nature.

Was a return visit from many years back. Glad that it is very well-maintained and much improved. We ended the trip with the the seaside route towards the visitor center as the endpoint, where we took bus back to Kranji MRT.

Highly recommended. There were barely any slopes and very family-friendly. Do remember to bring insect repellent and sunblock, binoculars for bird watchers and maybe a camera to capture some moments with your loved ones.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great place for kids to learn about mangrove environment and can see some animals upclose. The highlight is the mud walk.try to come before the high tide where the muddy area will be cover by sea water. Wear insect patch or repellent. Since it's a nature reserve just keep be abit alert at all times coz there are some monkey or even snake sightings if h r lucky

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Great place for bird photographer s and bird watchers. Very nice and relaxing place. Free car park. Well arranged hiding point to shoot and watch birds. 2 hours walking distance from start to end. The season for migration birds are September to March. Place is nice to visit with family and childeren. Public transport is available. Mobile will go roaming when you are there.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Singapore maybe a city within a garden, but it is the few wetlands that throughly brings out the natural beauty of natural habitat. At Sungei Buloh one can see not only the birds, flowers and insects, but the monitor lizards and crocodiles üêä as well. Open from 7am to 7 pm, it‚Äôs a nature photographer‚Äôs paradise. There‚Äôs a little cafe that serves local cuisine and an air conditioned visitor centre museum within the compound. The hike along the 3 km paths are easy for a family day fun walk. It‚Äôs a place to come and get away from the crowded city.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: If you love nature, you'll love it here. üòä I also like that they added a touch of beautiful structure there.. makes the place instragramble in every angle.  And it is a unique place. A lot of different kinds of migratory birds you can observe from a far.

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve

review_text: Definitely a nice place to take family too but have to make sure that you are going early in the morning.  Bring lots of mosquito repellent spray/patches/band as it is infested with them.  And water too because it does get hot by around 10am

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text: Awesome place to see wild Singapore crocodiles. Had 2 sightings of 2 crocs during my visit. Well organised park. Only problem was inadequate parking....

name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
review_text:
